    "Recommended approach: non-blocking, durable, queryable, late signals, and PII masking.",
    "Logging should not be performed synchronously on the request path.",
    "Log records should be enqueued immediately, with persistence and upload happening in the background.",
    "A short in-process buffer and background worker should batch and send logs to the durable store.",
    "This background approach should prevent per-message latency from being affected.",
    "The background uploader should retry and be idempotent so transient failures do not lose logs.",
    "Structured logs should be persisted as JSON rows in a data-warehouse or observability store such as Langsmith.",
    "Logs should be append-only and timestamped.",
    "Logs should be partitioned by date and indexed on conversation_id, session_id, and user_id.",
    "Logs should be queryable by conversation, user, turn, time range, or signal type.",
    "A Conversation table or object should store one row per session or conversation.",
    "Conversation_id should be the primary key for Conversation.",
    "Conversation records should include session_id, user_id, created_at, ended_at, and meta.",
    "User_id should be masked or pseudonymized as required.",
    "The meta field should store JSON such as channel, locale, model_version, and initial_prompt.",
    "A Turn or Message table or object should store one row per user or assistant turn.",
    "Turn_id should be unique within a conversation.",
    "Turn records should include conversation_id, session_id, user_id, parent_turn_id, role, timestamp, text_masked, pii_present, pii_fields, and metadata.",
    "Turn role values can include user, assistant, or system.",
    "Text stored for turns should be masked after PII masking.",
    "Pii_present should indicate whether PII was found.",
    "Pii_fields should list field types such as phone, card, dob, or aadhaar.",
    "Metadata may include embeddings, tokens, model_latency_ms, model_version, and assist_flags.",
    "A Late_Signals table or object should store events that may arrive after the conversation.",
    "Late signal records should include signal_id, conversation_id, turn_id, signal_type, source, timestamp_received, event_payload_masked, resolved_flag, severity, notes, and linked_support_id.",
    "Conversation_id is the primary linkage for late attachment.",
    "Turn_id is optional for late signals if the signal maps to a specific turn.",
    "Signal types can include escalation, email_reply, ticket_opened, refund, or survey.",
    "Sources can include email, support-ticket-system, or manual-label.",
    "Event payloads for late signals should be masked.",
    "A PII Audit table or object is optional.",
    "PII audit records should include audit_id, conversation_id, turn_id, pii_type, mask_pattern_used, mask_timestamp, and reason.",
    "Late signals must include conversation_id or enough metadata to resolve to a conversation_id.",
    "When a late signal arrives, it should be attached as a Late_Signals row with foreign keys to Conversation and Turn.",
    "Conversation or turn aggregates should be updated when late signals arrive.",
    "Original chronology should be preserved using timestamp_received.",
    "The time when a late signal maps to an older conversation should also be stored.",
